article.headline: Wheeler leads Wildcats in Fiesta Bowl Classic championship
article.linkText: Home sweet home: Arizona wins 32nd straight
article.story:
TUCSON, Ariz. (Ticker) -- Dee-Dee Wheeler and No. 25 Arizona had few problems running their home winning streak to 32 games.

Wheeler scored 20 points on 9-of-14 shooting as Arizona routed Weber State, 80-53, in a matchup of Wildcats in the championship game of the Fiesta Bowl Classic.

In the 14 years of the tournament, Arizona has won it 10 times.

Shawntinice Polk added 14 points and seven rebounds and Natalie Jones chipped in 10 and 11 for Arizona (5-1), which outrebounded Weber State, 49-30.

Arizona shot 46 percent (31-of-67) and limited Weber State (4-1) to just 26 percent (14-of-55).

Arizona evened the all-time series, 4-4. The schools had not met since Dec. 10, 1995, when Arizona cruised to a 92-46 victory.
